Research Data Consultations

Introduction

Research data consultations are booked in 1 hour blocks. Students are encouraged to return throughout project development, including during planning, collection, cleaning and analysis, and presentation. To help maintain a focus on learning, students deposit data on UBC’s OneDrive, where consultants, when possible, help with demonstration code on only a subset of the deposited data.

UBCO Biology funding started September, 2024, with 1 TA position in W1 and 2 TA positions in W2.

Feedback

  • “The explanation of new ideas and resources to help me with my research [was helpful].”
  • “[The consultant] modeled how to do the next steps and ensured I understood before the end of the session. [They] seemed committed to helping find the best solutions for my struggles.”
  • “[Learning] [h]ow to treat sparse data [was helpful].”
  • “Talking through the steps of reporting a model-based analysis…it was very good, couldn’t have been better.”
  • “[The consultant] helped me to think about my research from other directions and consider how to best analyze the data before any is even collected. [They] really encouraged me to think through all the potential effects on my study system so that I don’t look back and wish I had collected data on a certain variable. I have begun to make a causal flowchart like [they] suggested, which is really helping me.”
  • “[The consultant] explained to me what type of model to use, why we use it and how to use it. It helped me understand my data and conclude something.”
  • “[The consultant] gave a suggestion on what kind of plot is best how to visualize my data.”
